enerates wonder (thaumas), which, according to Socrates, is nothing other than the beginning of philosophy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aSophists (Greek philosophy). 4aPhilosophy : Ancient Greek Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Plato. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143845619540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438456195423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438456195/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles